,{"section":12,"text":"The description here mentions mucosal erosions, so that fits.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046025,0.082758,0.091334,0.094557,0.093616,0.091251,0.090766,0.087579,0.086,0.083882,0.07611,0.076121],"unified_progress":[0.053896,0.069142,0.080194,0.089566,0.093658,0.094372,0.093154,0.092686,0.091128,0.087392,0.080947,0.073865]},{"section":13,"text":"The hemorrhagic spots could be due to the erosions leading to bleeding.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036291,0.071705,0.081797,0.089534,0.094156,0.096866,0.099041,0.095154,0.093705,0.087226,0.081024,0.073502],"unified_progress":[0.043058,0.059234,0.072797,0.082137,0.09019,0.095288,0.096302,0.097386,0.099529,0.096224,0.090594,0.077262]},{"section":14,"text":"Since there's no ulceration, which is deeper, this points more towards erosive esophagitis or NSAID-induced gastritis.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038417,0.075849,0.085968,0.09215,0.093829,0.094311,0.094828,0.09141,0.090778,0.086982,0.077968,0.077511],"unified_progress":[0.041206,0.063166,0.077881,0.088087,0.093325,0.096887,0.096992,0.095714,0.095543,0.091244,0.083769,0.076187]},{"section":15,"text":"Another possibility could be Mallory-Weiss tears, but those are usually from forceful vomiting and would have different locations and presentation.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029739,0.065445,0.077837,0.087162,0.094029,0.09814,0.10255,0.10169,0.098284,0.095128,0.084548,0.065446],"unified_progress":[0.032339,0.060992,0.077323,0.087012,0.095713,0.10128,0.10196,0.10395,0.10144,0.10111,0.081073,0.055819]},{"section":16,"text":"The patient's history of NSAIDs is a big clue here.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034008,0.071312,0.085134,0.091272,0.094303,0.097598,0.095207,0.094286,0.090952,0.093299,0.082165,0.070465],"unified_progress":[0.066541,0.092139,0.086856,0.087666,0.088469,0.089403,0.091769,0.091006,0.086635,0.086946,0.07458,0.05799]},{"section":17,"text":"Also, the location in the stomach makes me think more of gastritis.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039244,0.077432,0.08916,0.094429,0.093826,0.092389,0.092118,0.089304,0.09315,0.086941,0.077758,0.074249],"unified_progress":[0.050163,0.072506,0.084925,0.096607,0.097496,0.095236,0.09541,0.091397,0.092462,0.085988,0.074041,0.063771]},{"section":18,"text":"Wait, there's a specific term for this.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027576,0.060357,0.079907,0.089115,0.096358,0.098001,0.098194,0.097455,0.098152,0.09282,0.085846,0.076218],"unified_progress":[0.038149,0.074482,0.086909,0.10125,0.098583,0.0936,0.0972,0.09188,0.088057,0.094168,0.075735,0.059987]},{"section":19,"text":"NSAID-induced gastropathy often presents with erosions and petechiae or pinpoint hemorrhages.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033396,0.066856,0.077347,0.088027,0.09552,0.09963,0.10119,0.096919,0.093142,0.090857,0.08089,0.07622],"unified_progress":[0.042352,0.062531,0.07916,0.091183,0.097107,0.1054,0.099522,0.097554,0.093597,0.087425,0.076344,0.067822]},{"section":20,"text":"The term \"punctate hemorrhagic areas\" matches that description.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036835,0.071539,0.080498,0.086348,0.090249,0.092887,0.094913,0.093484,0.094155,0.090028,0.085537,0.083528],"unified_progress":[0.044148,0.06521,0.07789,0.086747,0.092688,0.096561,0.095149,0.094933,0.094602,0.08908,0.085005,0.077987]},{"section":21,"text":"So putting it all together: NSAID use leading to gastric mucosal erosions with hemorrhage, no ulcers.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032307,0.062499,0.072177,0.079208,0.084007,0.087637,0.091456,0.091532,0.095176,0.094015,0.095297,0.11469],"unified_progress":[0.037116,0.051497,0.063194,0.073036,0.07875,0.085591,0.087384,0.092339,0.097548,0.098077,0.11024,0.12522]},{"section":22,"text":"The diagnosis should be NSAID-induced gastritis or erosive gastritis due to NSAIDs.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023012,0.046894,0.056472,0.064978,0.073553,0.08095,0.088056,0.091795,0.098804,0.10122,0.11161,0.16266],"unified_progress":[0.022036,0.034545,0.04462,0.053804,0.059997,0.07239,0.075953,0.088861,0.10047,0.10855,0.14351,0.19526]},{"section":23,"text":"Alternatively, could it be something like Curling's ulcer?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023308,0.050631,0.06402,0.074386,0.086266,0.092599,0.099626,0.10684,0.10857,0.10931,0.1034,0.081044],"unified_progress":[0.030326,0.056167,0.072175,0.083738,0.089595,0.093998,0.10042,0.10497,0.10606,0.10482,0.091586,0.066147]},{"section":24,"text":"That's related to burns or systemic disease, not NSAIDs.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022658,0.052962,0.067922,0.079709,0.090564,0.098264,0.10451,0.10666,0.1045,0.10386,0.095011,0.073383],"unified_progress":[0.039224,0.064825,0.075902,0.082622,0.091577,0.096965,0.099858,0.10454,0.10171,0.10125,0.083877,0.057658]},{"section":25,"text":"Zollinger-Ellison syndrome causes ulcers due to excess acid, but again, the key here is the NSAID use and the absence of ulcers.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024952,0.056719,0.070864,0.08259,0.091649,0.097896,0.10397,0.10385,0.10111,0.10108,0.090952,0.074362],"unified_progress":[0.033391,0.059004,0.076263,0.085552,0.094143,0.10059,0.10189,0.10398,0.10148,0.10081,0.0833,0.059604]},{"section":26,"text":"Yeah, definitely NSAID-related gastropathy.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02532,0.051686,0.063307,0.072273,0.080305,0.085906,0.091694,0.094241,0.097565,0.099227,0.10305,0.13543],"unified_progress":[0.029231,0.042435,0.053143,0.063716,0.069301,0.080119,0.082718,0.091233,0.096638,0.10271,0.12779,0.16097]}